Sentencas: The thermal, electrical, and fluid flow fields associated with a Siemens Power Generation Inc., Stationary Fuel Cells, flattened tubular high power density (HPD) solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) were investigated comprehensively in a previous study.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: The present computational investigation is the subsequent part of an ongoing numerical pursuit at Siemens of an optimized cell geometry, commercialization of SOFC technology being the ultimate objective.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: A Delta type HPD cell featuring eight air channels was investigated and compared with a flattened tubular HPD cell.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: The computational models were developed using the commercial computational fluid dynamics software FLUENT 6.2 along with its SOFC user defined routine to model the electrochemical effects.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: The SOFC model parameters were derived from experimental data.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: The cathode, the anode, and the interconnection layers of the cell were resolved in the model and all modes of heat transfer, conduction, convection, and radiation were included.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: The resulting electrical performance and the thermal hydraulic characteristics of the cells for fully reformed natural gas fuel flow (reformed external to the cell) are presented and discussed.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell

Sentencas: It was clear from these studies that the Delta HPD cell has distinct advantages over the flattened HPD cell in terms of system electrical performance as well as power density.
Titulo: Numerical Investigation of a Delta High Power Density Cell and Comparison With a Flattened Tubular High Power Density Cell
